bulbasaur.name: bulbasaur
bulbasaur.entry_text: For some time after its birth, itgrows by gaining nourishment fromthe seed on its back.  ~ Pokemon WHITE

ivysaur.name: ivysaur
ivysaur.entry_text: Exposure to sunlight adds to its strength.Sunlight also makes the bud on its backgrow larger.  ~ Pokemon SHIELD

venusaur.name: venusaur
venusaur.entry_text: Its plant blooms when it is absorbingsolar energy. It stays on the move toseek sunlight.  ~ Pokemon LEAFGREEN

charmander.name: charmander
charmander.entry_text: The flame on itstail indicatesCHARMANDER's life force. If it ishealthy, the flameburns brightly.  ~ Pokemon SILVER

charmeleon.name: charmeleon
charmeleon.entry_text: It lashes about with its tail to knockdown its foe. It then tears up the fallenopponent with sharp claws.  ~ Pokemon FIRERED

charizard.name: charizard
charizard.entry_text: It is said that CHARIZARD’s fireburns hotter if it hasexperienced harsh battles.  ~ Pokemon PEARL

squirtle.name: squirtle
squirtle.entry_text: When it feels threatened, it draws its limbs insideits shell and sprays water from its mouth.  ~ Pokemon SHIELD

wartortle.name: wartortle
wartortle.entry_text: It cleverly controls its furry ears and tail tomaintain its balance while swimming.  ~ Pokemon SHIELD

blastoise.name: blastoise
blastoise.entry_text: The waterspouts that protrude from itsshell are highly accurate. Their bullets ofwater can precisely nail tin cans froma distance of over 160 feet.  ~ Pokemon EMERALD

caterpie.name: caterpie
caterpie.entry_text: It releases a stench from its redantenna to repel enemies. Itgrows by molting repeatedly.  ~ Pokemon WHITE-2

metapod.name: metapod
metapod.entry_text: It prepares for evolution by hardeningits shell as much as possibleto protect its soft body.  ~ Pokemon SOULSILVER

butterfree.name: butterfree
butterfree.entry_text: Crystallized Gigantamax energy makes up thisPokémon’s blindingly bright and highlytoxic scales.  ~ Pokemon SWORD

weedle.name: weedle
weedle.entry_text: Often found in forests, eating leaves.It has a sharp stinger on its head thatinjects poison.  ~ Pokemon LEAFGREEN

kakuna.name: kakuna
kakuna.entry_text: From this form,it will grow intoan adult. As its body becomes soft­er, the externalshell hardens.  ~ Pokemon SILVER

beedrill.name: beedrill
beedrill.entry_text: Its best attack involves flyingaround at high speed, striking withpoison needles, then flying off.  ~ Pokemon WHITE

pidgey.name: pidgey
pidgey.entry_text: A common sight inforests and woods.It flaps its wings at groundlevel to kick upblinding sand.  ~ Pokemon RED

pidgeotto.name: pidgeotto
pidgeotto.entry_text: It flies over its wide territory insearch of prey, downing itwith its highly developed claws.  ~ Pokemon WHITE

pidgeot.name: pidgeot
pidgeot.entry_text: By flapping its wings with all itsmight, Pidgeot can make a gust ofwind capable of bending tall trees.  ~ Pokemon WHITE

rattata.name: rattata
rattata.entry_text: This POKéMON'simpressive vital­ity allows it to live anywhere. Italso multipliesvery quickly.  ~ Pokemon CRYSTAL

raticate.name: raticate
raticate.entry_text: Its hind feet are webbed, so it’s a strongswimmer. It can cross rivers and sometimeseven oceans.  ~ Pokemon SUN

spearow.name: spearow
spearow.entry_text: Farmers whose fields are troubled by bugPokémon appreciate Spearow for its vigorousappetite and look after it.  ~ Pokemon MOON

fearow.name: fearow
fearow.entry_text: It cleverly uses its thin, longbeak to pluck and eat small insectsthat hide under the ground.  ~ Pokemon SOULSILVER

ekans.name: ekans
ekans.entry_text: It sneaks through grass withoutmaking a sound and strikesunsuspecting prey from behind.  ~ Pokemon WHITE

arbok.name: arbok
arbok.entry_text: The pattern on its belly appears to be afrightening face. Weak foes will flee justat the sight of the pattern.  ~ Pokemon FIRERED

pikachu.name: pikachu
pikachu.entry_text: When several ofthese POKéMONgather, their electricity couldbuild and causelightning storms.  ~ Pokemon BLUE

raichu.name: raichu
raichu.entry_text: When its electricity builds, itsmuscles are stimulated, and it becomesmore aggressive than usual.  ~ Pokemon HEARTGOLD

sandshrew.name: sandshrew
sandshrew.entry_text: Its ice-covered body lets it slide across theground with bullet-like speed, sending itsenemies flying when it hits them.  ~ Pokemon LETS-GO-EEVEE

sandslash.name: sandslash
sandslash.entry_text: This is Sandslash’s form after adaptation to afrigid environment. The cold air emitted by itsbody sharpens its icy spikes.  ~ Pokemon LETS-GO-PIKACHU

nidoran\u2640.name: nidoran♀
nidoran\u2640.entry_text: While it does not prefer to fight,even one drop of the poison itsecretes from barbs can be fatal.  ~ Pokemon WHITE

nidorina.name: nidorina
nidorina.entry_text: It has a calm and caring nature.Because its horn grows slowly, itprefers not to fight.  ~ Pokemon SOULSILVER

nidoqueen.name: nidoqueen
nidoqueen.entry_text: NIDOQUEEN’s body is encased inextremely hard scales. It is adept atsending foes flying with harsh tackles. This POKéMON is at its strongest whenit is defending its young.  ~ Pokemon SAPPHIRE

nidoran\u2642.name: nidoran♂
nidoran\u2642.entry_text: Its large earsare always keptupright. If it senses danger, itwill attack with apoisonous sting.  ~ Pokemon YELLOW

nidorino.name: nidorino
nidorino.entry_text: It has a violent disposition andstabs foes with its horn, whichoozes poison upon impact.  ~ Pokemon PEARL

nidoking.name: nidoking
nidoking.entry_text: One swing of its mighty tail cansnap a telephone pole as if it werea matchstick.  ~ Pokemon PEARL

clefairy.name: clefairy
clefairy.entry_text: Its adorable appearance makes it popularas a pet. However, it is rare anddifficult to find.  ~ Pokemon FIRERED

clefable.name: clefable
clefable.entry_text: Its hearing is so acute it canhear a pin drop over half a mileaway. It lives on quiet mountains.  ~ Pokemon PEARL

vulpix.name: vulpix
vulpix.entry_text: While young, it has six gorgeous tails. When itgrows, several new tails are sprouted.  ~ Pokemon Y

ninetales.name: ninetales
ninetales.entry_text: Its nine tails are said to beimbued with a mystic power.It can live for a thousand years.  ~ Pokemon PLATINUM

jigglypuff.name: jigglypuff
jigglypuff.entry_text: Uses its alluringeyes to enraptureits foe. It then sings a pleasingmelody that lullsthe foe to sleep.  ~ Pokemon YELLOW

wigglytuff.name: wigglytuff
wigglytuff.entry_text: The body is soft and rubbery. Whenangered, it will suck in air and inflateitself to an enormous size.  ~ Pokemon LEAFGREEN

zubat.name: zubat
zubat.entry_text: During the day, itgathers withothers and hangs from the ceilingsof old buildingsand caves.  ~ Pokemon CRYSTAL

golbat.name: golbat
golbat.entry_text: GOLBAT bites down on prey with its fourfangs and drinks the victim’s blood.It becomes active on inky dark moonless nights, flying around toattack people and POKéMON.  ~ Pokemon SAPPHIRE

oddish.name: oddish
oddish.entry_text: During the daytime, ODDISH buriesitself in soil to absorb nutrients from the ground using its entire body. The more fertile the soil, the glossierits leaves become.  ~ Pokemon RUBY

gloom.name: gloom
gloom.entry_text: Smells incredibly foul! However, around oneout of a thousand people enjoy sniffingits nose-bending stink.  ~ Pokemon LETS-GO-PIKACHU

vileplume.name: vileplume
vileplume.entry_text: The larger itspetals, the moretoxic pollen it contains. Its bighead is heavy andhard to hold up.  ~ Pokemon RED

paras.name: paras

parasect.name: parasect
parasect.entry_text: A mushroom grown larger than thehost’s body controls Parasect.It scatters poisonous spores.  ~ Pokemon BLACK-2

venonat.name: venonat
venonat.entry_text: Its big eyes are actually clustersof tiny eyes. At night, its kind isdrawn by light.  ~ Pokemon PEARL

venomoth.name: venomoth
venomoth.entry_text: The powder on itswings is poisonousif it is dark in color. If it islight, it causesparalysis.  ~ Pokemon SILVER

diglett.name: diglett

dugtrio.name: dugtrio
dugtrio.entry_text: In battle, it digs through the ground andstrikes the unsuspecting foe from anunexpected direction.  ~ Pokemon FIRERED

meowth.name: meowth
meowth.entry_text: Meowth withdraws its sharp claws into its paws to slinkily sneakabout without making any incriminating footsteps.For some reason, this Pokémon loves shiny coins thatglitter with light.  ~ Pokemon OMEGA-RUBY

persian.name: persian
persian.entry_text: It has the classiest coat. The rippling of its furin the heat of battle has a beauty all its own.  ~ Pokemon LETS-GO-PIKACHU

psyduck.name: psyduck
psyduck.entry_text: If it uses its mysterious power,PSYDUCK can’t remember having done so.It apparently can’t form a memory of such an event because it goes intoan altered state that is much likedeep sleep.  ~ Pokemon SAPPHIRE

golduck.name: golduck
golduck.entry_text: It is seen swimming dynamically andelegantly using its well-developedlimbs and flippers.  ~ Pokemon PLATINUM

mankey.name: mankey
mankey.entry_text: It’s unsafe to approach if it getsviolently enraged for no reason andcan’t distinguish friends from foes.  ~ Pokemon SOULSILVER

primeape.name: primeape
primeape.entry_text: It is always outrageously furious. If itgives chase, it will tenaciously track thetarget no matter how far.  ~ Pokemon FIRERED

growlithe.name: growlithe
growlithe.entry_text: Growlithe has a superb sense of smell. Once it smells anything,this Pokémon won’t forget the scent, no matter what. It usesits advanced olfactory sense to determine the emotions ofother living things.  ~ Pokemon ALPHA-SAPPHIRE

arcanine.name: arcanine
arcanine.entry_text: Its proud and regal appearancehas captured the hearts ofpeople since long ago.  ~ Pokemon PLATINUM

poliwag.name: poliwag
poliwag.entry_text: Its newly grownlegs prevent itfrom running. It appears to preferswimming thantrying to stand.  ~ Pokemon RED

poliwhirl.name: poliwhirl
poliwhirl.entry_text: The spiral pattern on its bellysubtly undulates. Staring at itgradually causes drowsiness.  ~ Pokemon DIAMOND

poliwrath.name: poliwrath
poliwrath.entry_text: A swimmer adept at both the front crawl andbreaststroke. Easily overtakes the besthuman swimmers.  ~ Pokemon Y

abra.name: abra
abra.entry_text: Using its psychic power is such astrain on its brain that it needsto sleep for 18 hours a day.  ~ Pokemon WHITE

kadabra.name: kadabra
kadabra.entry_text: It possesses strong spiritual power.The more danger it faces,the stronger its psychic power.  ~ Pokemon HEARTGOLD

alakazam.name: alakazam
alakazam.entry_text: Closing both its eyes heightens allits other senses. This enables it touse its abilities to their extremes.  ~ Pokemon HEARTGOLD

machop.name: machop
machop.entry_text: Always brimmingwith power, itpasses time by lifting boulders.Doing so makes iteven stronger.  ~ Pokemon GOLD

machoke.name: machoke
machoke.entry_text: It can lift a dump truck with one hand. Using thatpower, it helps people with heavy jobs.  ~ Pokemon Y

machamp.name: machamp
machamp.entry_text: Its four muscled arms slam foeswith powerful punches and chopsat blinding speed.  ~ Pokemon BLACK

bellsprout.name: bellsprout
bellsprout.entry_text: Prefers hot andhumid places.It ensnares tiny insects with itsvines and devoursthem.  ~ Pokemon YELLOW

weepinbell.name: weepinbell

victreebel.name: victreebel
victreebel.entry_text: It pools in its mouth a fluid witha honeylike scent, which is reallyan acid that dissolves anything.  ~ Pokemon WHITE

tentacool.name: tentacool

tentacruel.name: tentacruel
tentacruel.entry_text: Its 80 tentaclesabsorb water andstretch almost endlessly to CON­STRICT its preyand enemies.  ~ Pokemon GOLD

geodude.name: geodude
geodude.entry_text: Its stone head is imbued with electricity andmagnetism. If you carelessly step on one,you’ll be in for a painful shock.  ~ Pokemon LETS-GO-PIKACHU

graveler.name: graveler
graveler.entry_text: It tumbles down slopes, heedlessof any body parts chipping off.It eats a ton of rocks daily.  ~ Pokemon PEARL

golem.name: golem
golem.entry_text: It is said to live in volcanic craterson mountain peaks. Once a year, it shedsits hide and grows larger. The shed hidecrumbles and returns to the soil.  ~ Pokemon EMERALD

ponyta.name: ponyta
ponyta.entry_text: About an hour after birth, itsfiery mane and tail grow out,giving it an impressive appearance.  ~ Pokemon DIAMOND

rapidash.name: rapidash
rapidash.entry_text: It gallops at nearly 150 mph.With its mane blazing ferociously,it races as if it were an arrow.  ~ Pokemon DIAMOND

slowpoke.name: slowpoke
slowpoke.entry_text: Slowpoke uses its tail to catch prey by dipping it in waterat the side of a river. However, this Pokémon often forgetswhat it’s doing and often spends entire days just loafingat water’s edge.  ~ Pokemon ALPHA-SAPPHIRE

slowbro.name: slowbro
slowbro.entry_text: Lives lazily by the sea. If the Shellder on its tailcomes off, it becomes a Slowpoke again.  ~ Pokemon LETS-GO-EEVEE

magnemite.name: magnemite
magnemite.entry_text: The electromagnetic waves emitted bythe units at the sides of its head expelantigravity, which allows it to float.  ~ Pokemon WHITE-2

magneton.name: magneton
magneton.entry_text: This Pokémon is three Magnemite that havelinked together. Magneton sends out powerfulradio waves to study its surroundings.  ~ Pokemon SWORD

farfetchd.name: farfetchd
farfetchd.entry_text: FARFETCH’D is always seen with a stickfrom a plant of some sort. Apparently,there are good sticks and bad sticks. This POKéMON has been known to fightwith others over sticks.  ~ Pokemon RUBY

doduo.name: doduo
doduo.entry_text: It lives on agrassy plain whereit can see a long way. If it sees anenemy, it runsaway at 60 mph.  ~ Pokemon CRYSTAL

dodrio.name: dodrio
dodrio.entry_text: It collects data and plans threetimes as wisely, but it may thinktoo much and be­come immobilized.  ~ Pokemon GOLD

seel.name: seel
seel.entry_text: A Pokémon that lives on icebergs.It swims in the sea using the pointon its head to break up ice.  ~ Pokemon PEARL

dewgong.name: dewgong

grimer.name: grimer
grimer.entry_text: As it moves, itloses bits of itsbody from which new GRIMER emerge.This worsens thestench around it.  ~ Pokemon GOLD

muk.name: muk
muk.entry_text: This POKéMON’s favorite food isanything that is repugnantly filthy.In dirty towns where people think nothing of throwing away litter on thestreets, MUK are certain to gather.  ~ Pokemon SAPPHIRE

shellder.name: shellder

cloyster.name: cloyster

gastly.name: gastly

haunter.name: haunter
haunter.entry_text: It can slip through any obstacle.It lurks inside walls to keep aneye on its foes.  ~ Pokemon DIAMOND

gengar.name: gengar

onix.name: onix
onix.entry_text: Opening its large mouth, it ingestsmassive amounts of soil and createslong tunnels.  ~ Pokemon BLACK-2

drowzee.name: drowzee

hypno.name: hypno
hypno.entry_text: When it locks eyeswith an enemy, itwill use a mix of PSI moves such asHYPNOSIS andCONFUSION.  ~ Pokemon BLUE

krabby.name: krabby
krabby.entry_text: It can be found near the sea. The large pincersgrow back if they are torn out of their sockets.  ~ Pokemon Y

kingler.name: kingler
kingler.entry_text: It waves its huge, oversized claw in theair to communicate with others.But since the claw is so heavy, thisPOKéMON quickly tires.  ~ Pokemon EMERALD

voltorb.name: voltorb
voltorb.entry_text: It is said to camouflage itself as a Poké Ball.It will self-destruct with very little stimulus.  ~ Pokemon LETS-GO-EEVEE

electrode.name: electrode
electrode.entry_text: It stores electricenergy under veryhigh pressure. It often explodeswith little or noprovocation.  ~ Pokemon RED

exeggcute.name: exeggcute
exeggcute.entry_text: Its six eggs converse usingtelepathy. They can quickly gatherif they become separated.  ~ Pokemon WHITE-2

exeggutor.name: exeggutor
exeggutor.entry_text: Each of its heads has its own will. They usetelepathy to discuss their plans before comingto a joint decision.  ~ Pokemon SUN

cubone.name: cubone
cubone.entry_text: It wears the skull of its dead mother onits head. When it becomes lonesome, it issaid to cry loudly.  ~ Pokemon FIRERED

marowak.name: marowak
marowak.entry_text: From its birth, this savage Pokémonconstantly holds bones. It isskilled in using them as weapons.  ~ Pokemon DIAMOND

hitmonlee.name: hitmonlee
hitmonlee.entry_text: Its legs can stretch double.First-time foes are startled byits extensible reach.  ~ Pokemon DIAMOND

hitmonchan.name: hitmonchan
hitmonchan.entry_text: Its punches slicethe air. They arelaunched at such high speed, even aslight graze couldcause a burn.  ~ Pokemon SILVER

lickitung.name: lickitung

koffing.name: koffing
koffing.entry_text: Its thin, balloon-like body is inflated by horriblytoxic gases. It reeks when it is nearby.  ~ Pokemon X

weezing.name: weezing
weezing.entry_text: By diluting its toxic gases with a specialprocess, the highest grade of perfume canbe extracted. To WEEZING, gases emanatingfrom garbage are the ultimate feast.  ~ Pokemon EMERALD

rhyhorn.name: rhyhorn
rhyhorn.entry_text: Its massive bones are 1,000 times harderthan human bones. Its TACKLE can knock asemitrailer flying.  ~ Pokemon LEAFGREEN

rhydon.name: rhydon

chansey.name: chansey
chansey.entry_text: It lays several eggs a day. The eggs are apparentlyrich in nutrients and extremely delicious.  ~ Pokemon Y

tangela.name: tangela
tangela.entry_text: It tangles any moving thing with its vines. Theirsubtle shaking is ticklish if you get ensnared.  ~ Pokemon Y

kangaskhan.name: kangaskhan
kangaskhan.entry_text: Raises its youngin its bellypouch. Won't run from any fightto keep its youngprotected.  ~ Pokemon YELLOW

horsea.name: horsea
horsea.entry_text: It makes its nest in the shade ofcorals. If it senses danger, itspits murky ink and flees.  ~ Pokemon WHITE

seadra.name: seadra
seadra.entry_text: The male raisesthe young. If itis approached, it uses its toxicspikes to fend offthe intruder.  ~ Pokemon CRYSTAL

goldeen.name: goldeen
goldeen.entry_text: Though it appears very elegantwhen swimming with fins unfurled, itcan jab powerfully with its horn.  ~ Pokemon BLACK-2

seaking.name: seaking
seaking.entry_text: To attract females, males dance on the river’sfloor. The females gather around the male thatdances most gracefully.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-MOON

staryu.name: staryu

starmie.name: starmie
starmie.entry_text: Its core shines in many colorsand sends radio signals into spaceto communicate with something.  ~ Pokemon BLACK-2

mr. mime.name: mr. mime

scyther.name: scyther

jynx.name: jynx
jynx.entry_text: Its strange cries sound like human language.There are some musicians who compose songsfor Jynx to sing.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-MOON

electabuzz.name: electabuzz
electabuzz.entry_text: Electricity leaks from it in amounts far greaterthan the amount of electricity it eats.  ~ Pokemon MOON

magmar.name: magmar
magmar.entry_text: Its body alwaysburns with anorange glow that enables it tohide perfectlyamong flames.  ~ Pokemon BLUE

pinsir.name: pinsir
pinsir.entry_text: Grips its prey inits pincers andsqueezes hard! It can't move if it'scold, so it livesin warm places.  ~ Pokemon YELLOW

tauros.name: tauros
tauros.entry_text: This POKéMON is not satisfied unlessit is rampaging at all times.If there is no opponent for TAUROS to battle, it will charge at thick trees andknock them down to calm itself.  ~ Pokemon RUBY

magikarp.name: magikarp
magikarp.entry_text: Famous for beingvery unreliable.It can be found swimming in seas,lakes, rivers andshallow puddles.  ~ Pokemon YELLOW

gyarados.name: gyarados
gyarados.entry_text: In ancient literature, there is a record of a Gyaradosthat razed a village when violence flared.  ~ Pokemon X

lapras.name: lapras
lapras.entry_text: A POKéMON thathas been over­hunted almost to extinction. Itcan ferry peopleacross the water.  ~ Pokemon RED

ditto.name: ditto
ditto.entry_text: It has the ability to reconstituteits entire cellular structure totransform into whatever it sees.  ~ Pokemon PLATINUM

eevee.name: eevee
eevee.entry_text: Its genetic codeis unstable, so itcould evolve in a variety of ways.There are only afew alive.  ~ Pokemon YELLOW

vaporeon.name: vaporeon

jolteon.name: jolteon
jolteon.entry_text: The negativelycharged ionsgenerated in its fur create aconstant sparkingnoise.  ~ Pokemon CRYSTAL

flareon.name: flareon
flareon.entry_text: Once it has stored up enough heat, thisPokémon’s body temperature can reach up to1,700 degrees Fahrenheit.  ~ Pokemon SWORD

porygon.name: porygon

omanyte.name: omanyte

omastar.name: omastar
omastar.entry_text: It is thought that this Pokémonbecame extinct because its spiralshell grew too large.  ~ Pokemon WHITE-2

kabuto.name: kabuto
kabuto.entry_text: A POKéMON thatwas resurrectedfrom a fossil found in what wasonce the oceanfloor eons ago.  ~ Pokemon BLUE

kabutops.name: kabutops

aerodactyl.name: aerodactyl

snorlax.name: snorlax

articuno.name: articuno

zapdos.name: zapdos
zapdos.entry_text: A legendary Pokémon that is saidto live in thunderclouds. It freelycontrols lightning bolts.  ~ Pokemon BLACK-2

moltres.name: moltres
moltres.entry_text: One of the legendary bird Pokémon.It is said that its appearanceindicates the coming of spring.  ~ Pokemon BLACK

dratini.name: dratini
dratini.entry_text: It’s still weak, so it lurks on the floor of bodiesof water, eating whatever food sinks down andliving a quiet life.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-SUN

dragonair.name: dragonair
dragonair.entry_text: If its body takes on an aura, theweather changes instantly. It issaid to live in seas and lakes.  ~ Pokemon PLATINUM

dragonite.name: dragonite
dragonite.entry_text: An extremelyrarely seenmarine POKéMON. Its intelligenceis said to matchthat of humans.  ~ Pokemon BLUE

mewtwo.name: mewtwo
mewtwo.entry_text: It was created bya scientist afteryears of horrific gene splicing andDNA engineeringexperiments.  ~ Pokemon BLUE

mew.name: mew
mew.entry_text: Because it can use all kinds ofmoves, many scientists believe Mewto be the ancestor of Pokémon.  ~ Pokemon WHITE

chikorita.name: chikorita
chikorita.entry_text: Its pleasantlyaromatic leaveshave the ability to check the hu­midity and tem­perature.  ~ Pokemon SILVER

bayleef.name: bayleef
bayleef.entry_text: The buds that ring its neck giveoff a spicy aroma that perkspeople up.  ~ Pokemon PEARL

meganium.name: meganium
meganium.entry_text: MEGANIUM’s breath has the power to revivedead grass and plants. It can make themhealthy again.  ~ Pokemon FIRERED

cyndaquil.name: cyndaquil

quilava.name: quilava

totodile.name: totodile

furret.name: furret

hoothoot.name: hoothoot

noctowl.name: noctowl

ledian.name: ledian

chinchou.name: chinchou

pichu.name: pichu

cleffa.name: cleffa

igglybuff.name: igglybuff

bellossom.name: bellossom

azumarill.name: azumarill

politoed.name: politoed

aipom.name: aipom

granbull.name: granbull

shuckle.name: shuckle

lairon.name: lairon
lairon.entry_text: LAIRON tempers its steel body bydrinking highly nutritious mineralspringwater until it is bloated. This POKéMON makes its nest close tosprings of delicious water.  ~ Pokemon RUBY

aggron.name: aggron
aggron.entry_text: It claims a large mountain as its soleterritory. It mercilessly thrashes thosethat violate its space.  ~ Pokemon FIRERED

meditite.name: meditite
meditite.entry_text: Meditite undertakes rigorous mental training deep in themountains. However, whenever it meditates, this Pokémonalways loses its concentration and focus. As a result,its training never ends.  ~ Pokemon OMEGA-RUBY

medicham.name: medicham
medicham.entry_text: It gains the ability to see the auraof its opponents by honing its mindthrough starvation.  ~ Pokemon BLACK-2

electrike.name: electrike
electrike.entry_text: ELECTRIKE runs faster than the humaneye can follow. The friction fromrunning is converted into electricity, which is then stored in this POKéMON’sfur.  ~ Pokemon SAPPHIRE

manectric.name: manectric
manectric.entry_text: Because lightning falls in their vicinities,MANECTRIC were thought to have been bornfrom lightning. In battle, they createthunderclouds.  ~ Pokemon EMERALD

plusle.name: plusle
plusle.entry_text: It cheers on friends with pom-pomsmade of sparks. It drains powerfrom telephone poles.  ~ Pokemon BLACK-2

minun.name: minun
minun.entry_text: Its dislike of water makes it take shelterunder the eaves of houses in rain. It usespom-poms made of sparks for cheering.  ~ Pokemon LEAFGREEN

volbeat.name: volbeat
volbeat.entry_text: It lives around clean ponds. At night, its rear lightsup. It converses with others by flashing its light.  ~ Pokemon Y

illumise.name: illumise
illumise.entry_text: With its sweet aroma, it guidesVolbeat to draw signs with light inthe night sky.  ~ Pokemon WHITE-2

roselia.name: roselia
roselia.entry_text: Roselia that drink nutritionally rich springwater aresaid to reveal rare coloration when they bloom.  ~ Pokemon Y

gulpin.name: gulpin
gulpin.entry_text: Almost all its body is its stomach.Its harsh digestive juices quicklydissolve anything it swallows.  ~ Pokemon WHITE-2

swalot.name: swalot
swalot.entry_text: It swallows anything whole.It sweats toxic fluids from itsfollicles to douse foes.  ~ Pokemon PEARL

carvanha.name: carvanha
carvanha.entry_text: It lives in massive rivers that coursethrough jungles. It swarms prey thatenter its territory.  ~ Pokemon FIRERED

sharpedo.name: sharpedo
sharpedo.entry_text: It pursues its prey at speeds of 75 mph andfinishes them off with fangs that can crush iron.It is known as the bully of the sea.  ~ Pokemon SUN

wailmer.name: wailmer
wailmer.entry_text: It eats one ton of food every day.It plays by shooting stored seawaterout its blowholes with great force.  ~ Pokemon BLACK-2

wailord.name: wailord
wailord.entry_text: The biggest of all Pokémon.It can dive to a depth of almost10,000 feet on only one breath.  ~ Pokemon PEARL

numel.name: numel
numel.entry_text: Numel stores magma of almost 2,200 degrees Fahrenheitwithin its body. If it gets wet, the magma cools and hardens.In that event, the Pokémon’s body grows heavy and itsmovements become sluggish.  ~ Pokemon ALPHA-SAPPHIRE

camerupt.name: camerupt
camerupt.entry_text: If angered, the humps on its back eruptin a shower of molten lava. It lives inthe craters of volcanoes.  ~ Pokemon FIRERED

torkoal.name: torkoal
torkoal.entry_text: It burns coal inside its shell forenergy. It blows out black soot ifit is endangered.  ~ Pokemon BLACK-2

spoink.name: spoink
spoink.entry_text: It bounces constantly, using itstail like a spring. The shock ofbouncing keeps its heart beating.  ~ Pokemon BLACK

grumpig.name: grumpig
grumpig.entry_text: It uses black pearls to amplify itspsycho-power. It does an odddance to gain control over foes.  ~ Pokemon PLATINUM

spinda.name: spinda
spinda.entry_text: No two SPINDA have the samepattern of spots. Its totteringstep fouls the aim of foes.  ~ Pokemon DIAMOND

trapinch.name: trapinch
trapinch.entry_text: Trapinch’s nest is a sloped, bowl-like pit dug in sand.This Pokémon patiently waits for prey to tumble down the pit.Its giant jaws have enough strength to crush even boulders.  ~ Pokemon OMEGA-RUBY

vibrava.name: vibrava
vibrava.entry_text: It generates ultrasonic waves by violentlyflapping its wings. After making its preyfaint, it melts the prey with acid.  ~ Pokemon FIRERED

flygon.name: flygon
flygon.entry_text: It whips up sandstorms withpowerful flaps of its wings. It isknown as “The Desert Spirit.”  ~ Pokemon PLATINUM

cacnea.name: cacnea
cacnea.entry_text: It lives in arid locations. Its yellow flowers bloomonce a year.  ~ Pokemon X

cacturne.name: cacturne
cacturne.entry_text: It lives in deserts. It becomes active atnight when it hunts for prey exhaustedfrom the desert’s heat.  ~ Pokemon FIRERED

swablu.name: swablu
swablu.entry_text: Its wings bring cottony clouds tomind. It grooms with springwaterand loves to sit on heads.  ~ Pokemon HEARTGOLD

altaria.name: altaria
altaria.entry_text: Altaria dances and wheels through the sky among billowing,cotton-like clouds. By singing melodies in its crystal-clearvoice, this Pokémon makes its listeners experience dreamywonderment.  ~ Pokemon OMEGA-RUBY

zangoose.name: zangoose
zangoose.entry_text: ZANGOOSE usually stays on all fours,but when angered, it gets up on itshind legs and extends its claws. This POKéMON shares a bitter rivalrywith SEVIPER that dates back overgenerations.  ~ Pokemon SAPPHIRE

seviper.name: seviper
seviper.entry_text: Seviper shares a generations-long feud with Zangoose.The scars on its body are evidence of vicious battles.This Pokémon attacks using its sword-edged tail.  ~ Pokemon OMEGA-RUBY

lunatone.name: lunatone
lunatone.entry_text: The phase of the moon apparentlyhas some effect on its power.It’s active on the night of a full moon.  ~ Pokemon BLACK-2

solrock.name: solrock
solrock.entry_text: Solar energy is the source of its power,so it is strong during the daytime.When it spins, its body shines.  ~ Pokemon BLACK-2

barboach.name: barboach
barboach.entry_text: Its slimy body is hard to grasp. Inone region, it is said to have beenborn from hardened mud.  ~ Pokemon WHITE-2

whiscash.name: whiscash
whiscash.entry_text: A glutton that devours anything that moves,it quietly lurks at the bottom of swamps,lying in wait for prey.  ~ Pokemon SUN

corphish.name: corphish
corphish.entry_text: Individuals that have been set free by Trainerswho could no longer raise them have becomecommon, and they can now be found in Alola.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-SUN

crawdaunt.name: crawdaunt
crawdaunt.entry_text: A brutish Pokémon that loves tobattle. It will crash itself into anyfoe that approaches its nest.  ~ Pokemon HEARTGOLD

baltoy.name: baltoy
baltoy.entry_text: It moves by spinning on its foot.It is a rare Pokémon that wasdiscovered in ancient ruins.  ~ Pokemon WHITE

claydol.name: claydol
claydol.entry_text: This mysterious Pokémon started lifeas an ancient clay figurine made over20,000 years ago.  ~ Pokemon WHITE-2

lileep.name: lileep
lileep.entry_text: In ancient times, it lived in warm seas. Itdisguised itself as seaweed to ambush its preyand devoured them whole when they got close.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-SUN

cradily.name: cradily
cradily.entry_text: It lives in the shallows of warmseas. When the tide goes out, itdigs up prey from beaches.  ~ Pokemon WHITE-2

anorith.name: anorith
anorith.entry_text: It is a kind of Pokémon progenitor. It uses itsextending claws to catch prey hiding among rockson the seafloor.  ~ Pokemon X

armaldo.name: armaldo
armaldo.entry_text: It went ashore after evolving.Its entire body is clad in a sturdyarmor.  ~ Pokemon PEARL

feebas.name: feebas
feebas.entry_text: Although unattractive and unpopular, thisPokémon’s marvelous vitality has made it asubject of research.  ~ Pokemon SWORD

milotic.name: milotic
milotic.entry_text: Its lovely scales are described asrainbow colored. They change colordepending on the viewing angle.  ~ Pokemon PLATINUM

castform.name: castform
castform.entry_text: This Pokémon can change its cells,taking different forms based onthe temperature and humidity.  ~ Pokemon SOULSILVER

kecleon.name: kecleon
kecleon.entry_text: Its color changes for concealment and alsowhen its mood or health changes. The darkerthe color, the healthier it is.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-MOON

shuppet.name: shuppet
shuppet.entry_text: SHUPPET is attracted by feelingsof jealousy and vindictiveness.If someone develops strong feelings of vengeance, this POKéMON will appearin a swarm and line up beneath the eavesof that person’s home.  ~ Pokemon RUBY

banette.name: banette
banette.entry_text: A doll that became a Pokémon overits grudge of being thrown away. Itseeks the child who disowned it.  ~ Pokemon WHITE-2

duskull.name: duskull
duskull.entry_text: If it finds bad children who won’tlisten to their parents, it willspirit them away--or so it’s said.  ~ Pokemon HEARTGOLD

dusclops.name: dusclops
dusclops.entry_text: Its body is entirely hollow. When it opensits mouth, it sucks everything in as if itwere a black hole.  ~ Pokemon LEAFGREEN

tropius.name: tropius
tropius.entry_text: Children of the southern tropics eat as snacks the fruit thatgrows in bunches around the neck of Tropius. This Pokémonflies by flapping the leaves on its back as if they were wings.  ~ Pokemon ALPHA-SAPPHIRE

chimecho.name: chimecho
chimecho.entry_text: To knock foes flying, it makes theair shudder with its cries. Itconverses using seven cries.  ~ Pokemon DIAMOND

absol.name: absol
absol.entry_text: Every time Absol appears before people, it is followed by adisaster such as an earthquake or a tidal wave. As a result,it came to be known as the disaster Pokémon.  ~ Pokemon OMEGA-RUBY

wynaut.name: wynaut
wynaut.entry_text: It grows strong by pushing upagainst others en masse.It loves eating sweet fruit.  ~ Pokemon PEARL

snorunt.name: snorunt
snorunt.entry_text: It is said that several Snoruntgather under giant leaves andlive together in harmony.  ~ Pokemon BLACK

glalie.name: glalie
glalie.entry_text: It has a body of ice that won’t melt,even with fire. It can instantly freezemoisture in the atmosphere.  ~ Pokemon FIRERED

spheal.name: spheal
spheal.entry_text: It crosses the oceans by rolling itselfon drifting ice. Fluffy fur keeps it warmwhen the temperature is below freezing.  ~ Pokemon HEARTGOLD

sealeo.name: sealeo
sealeo.entry_text: It has a very sensitive nose.It touches new things with its noseto examine them.  ~ Pokemon SOULSILVER

walrein.name: walrein
walrein.entry_text: It shatters drift ice with itsstrong tusks. Its thick layer ofblubber repels enemy attacks.  ~ Pokemon HEARTGOLD

clamperl.name: clamperl
clamperl.entry_text: CLAMPERL’s sturdy shell is not only goodfor protection - it is also used forclamping and catching prey. A fully grown CLAMPERL’s shell will bescored with nicks and scratches allover.  ~ Pokemon RUBY

huntail.name: huntail
huntail.entry_text: It lives deep in the pitch-dark sea.It attracts prey by moving its tailin mimicry of a small animal.  ~ Pokemon HEARTGOLD

gorebyss.name: gorebyss
gorebyss.entry_text: Its swimming form is exquisitely elegant.With its thin mouth, it feeds on seaweedthat grows between rocks.  ~ Pokemon FIRERED

relicanth.name: relicanth
relicanth.entry_text: Discovered by chance duringdeep-sea explorations, it has notchanged since ancient times.  ~ Pokemon HEARTGOLD

luvdisc.name: luvdisc
luvdisc.entry_text: During the spawning season, countlessLUVDISC congregate at coral reefs,turning the waters pink.  ~ Pokemon LEAFGREEN

bagon.name: bagon
bagon.entry_text: Dreaming of one day flying, itpractices by leaping off cliffsevery day.  ~ Pokemon BLACK-2

shelgon.name: shelgon
shelgon.entry_text: Covering SHELGON’s body are outgrowthsmuch like bones. The shell is very hardand bounces off enemy attacks. When awaiting evolution, this POKéMONhides away in a cavern.  ~ Pokemon SAPPHIRE

salamence.name: salamence
salamence.entry_text: It’s uncontrollable if enraged.It flies around spouting flames andscorching fields and mountains.  ~ Pokemon HEARTGOLD

beldum.name: beldum
beldum.entry_text: It uses magnetic waves to converse withits kind. All the cells in its body aremagnetic.  ~ Pokemon FIRERED

metang.name: metang
metang.entry_text: The claws tipping its arms pack thedestructive power to tear through thickiron sheets as if they were silk. It fliesat over 60 miles per hour.  ~ Pokemon EMERALD

metagross.name: metagross
metagross.entry_text: A linkage of two Metang, this Pokémon canperform any calculation in a flash by utilizingparallel processing in its four brains.  ~ Pokemon MOON

regirock.name: regirock
regirock.entry_text: REGIROCK was sealed away by peoplelong ago. If this POKéMON’s body isdamaged in battle, it is said to seek out suitable rocks on its own to repairitself.  ~ Pokemon RUBY

regice.name: regice
regice.entry_text: Its body is made of ice from theice age. It controls frigid air of-328 degrees Fahrenheit.  ~ Pokemon DIAMOND

registeel.name: registeel
registeel.entry_text: Tempered by pressure undergroundover tens of thousands of years,its body cannot be scratched.  ~ Pokemon BLACK

latias.name: latias
latias.entry_text: Latias is highly sensitive to the emotions of people. If it sensesany hostility, this Pokémon ruffles the feathers all over its bodyand cries shrilly to intimidate the foe.  ~ Pokemon OMEGA-RUBY

latios.name: latios
latios.entry_text: It has a docile temperament and dislikesfighting. Tucking in its forelegs, it canfly faster than a jet plane.  ~ Pokemon FIRERED

kyogre.name: kyogre
kyogre.entry_text: KYOGRE has the power to create massiverain clouds that cover the entire skyand bring about torrential downpours. This POKéMON saved people who weresuffering from droughts.  ~ Pokemon RUBY

groudon.name: groudon
groudon.entry_text: It had been asleep in undergroundmagma ever since it fiercelyfought Kyogre long ago.  ~ Pokemon BLACK

rayquaza.name: rayquaza
rayquaza.entry_text: It lives in the ozone layer farabove the clouds and cannot beseen from the ground.  ~ Pokemon BLACK-2

jirachi.name: jirachi
jirachi.entry_text: A legend states that Jirachi will make true any wish that iswritten on notes attached to its head when it awakens. If thisPokémon senses danger, it will fight without awakening.  ~ Pokemon OMEGA-RUBY

deoxys.name: deoxys
deoxys.entry_text: An alien virus that fell to earthon a meteor underwent a DNAmutation to become this Pokémon.  ~ Pokemon BLACK

turtwig.name: turtwig
turtwig.entry_text: It undertakes photosynthesis with its body, makingoxygen. The leaf on its head wilts if it is thirsty.  ~ Pokemon Y

grotle.name: grotle
grotle.entry_text: A GROTLE that lives in the forestis said to have its own secretspringwater.  ~ Pokemon HEARTGOLD

torterra.name: torterra
torterra.entry_text: Small Pokémon occasionally gatheron its unmoving back to beginbuilding their nests.  ~ Pokemon DIAMOND

chimchar.name: chimchar
chimchar.entry_text: The gas made in its belly burns fromits rear end. The fire burns weaklywhen it feels sick.  ~ Pokemon SOULSILVER

monferno.name: monferno
monferno.entry_text: It skillfully controls the intensityof the fire on its tail to keep itsfoes at an ideal distance.  ~ Pokemon WHITE

infernape.name: infernape
infernape.entry_text: It tosses its enemies around withagility. It uses all its limbs tofight in its own unique style.  ~ Pokemon HEARTGOLD

piplup.name: piplup
piplup.entry_text: It lives along shores in northerncountries. A skilled swimmer, itdives for over 10 minutes to hunt.  ~ Pokemon PEARL

prinplup.name: prinplup
prinplup.entry_text: It lives a solitary life. Its wings deliver wicked blowsthat can snap even the thickest of trees.  ~ Pokemon Y

empoleon.name: empoleon
empoleon.entry_text: It avoids unnecessary disputes,but it will decimate anything thatthreatens its pride.  ~ Pokemon HEARTGOLD

starly.name: starly
starly.entry_text: Because they are weak individually,they form groups. However, theybicker if the group grows too big.  ~ Pokemon WHITE-2

staravia.name: staravia
staravia.entry_text: It lives in forests and fields. Squabbles overterritory occur when flocks collide.  ~ Pokemon Y

staraptor.name: staraptor
staraptor.entry_text: When STARAVIA evolve intoSTARAPTOR, they leave the flock tolive alone. They have sturdy wings.  ~ Pokemon SOULSILVER

bidoof.name: bidoof
bidoof.entry_text: With nerves of steel, nothing can perturb it. It ismore agile and active than it appears.  ~ Pokemon X

bibarel.name: bibarel
bibarel.entry_text: A river dammed by BIBAREL willnever overflow its banks, whichis appreciated by people nearby.  ~ Pokemon PLATINUM

kricketot.name: kricketot
kricketot.entry_text: Its legs are short. Whenever itstumbles, its stiff antennae clackwith a xylophone-like sound.  ~ Pokemon BLACK-2

kricketune.name: kricketune
kricketune.entry_text: There is a village that hosts acontest based on the amazinglyvariable cries of this Pokémon.  ~ Pokemon WHITE

shinx.name: shinx
shinx.entry_text: The extension and contraction ofits muscles generates electricity.It glows when in trouble.  ~ Pokemon WHITE-2

luxio.name: luxio
luxio.entry_text: Strong electricity courses throughthe tips of its sharp claws. A lightscratch causes fainting in foes.  ~ Pokemon PLATINUM

luxray.name: luxray
luxray.entry_text: When its eyes gleam gold, it can spot hidingprey—even those taking shelter behind a wall.  ~ Pokemon OMEGA-RUBY

budew.name: budew
budew.entry_text: This Pokémon is highly sensitive to temperaturechanges. When its bud starts to open, that meansspring is right around the corner.  ~ Pokemon SHIELD

roserade.name: roserade
roserade.entry_text: Luring prey with a sweet scent, ituses poison whips on its armsto poison, bind, and finish off the prey.  ~ Pokemon WHITE-2

cranidos.name: cranidos
cranidos.entry_text: A lifelong jungle dweller from 100million years ago, it would snapobstructing trees with head butts.  ~ Pokemon BLACK-2

rampardos.name: rampardos
rampardos.entry_text: This ancient Pokémon used headbutts skillfully.Its brain was really small, so some theoriessuggest that its stupidity led to its extinction.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-MOON

shieldon.name: shieldon
shieldon.entry_text: It is outstandingly armored. As aresult, it can eat grass andberries without having to fight.  ~ Pokemon WHITE

bastiodon.name: bastiodon
bastiodon.entry_text: It lived in the same environments as Rampardos.Their fossils have been found together—seemingly from after they’d fought to the finish.  ~ Pokemon MOON

burmy.name: burmy
burmy.entry_text: To shelter itself from cold, wintrywinds, it covers itself with a cloakmade of twigs and leaves.  ~ Pokemon DIAMOND

wormadam.name: wormadam
wormadam.entry_text: It is said that a WORMADAM thatevolves on a cold day will have athicker cloak.  ~ Pokemon SOULSILVER

mothim.name: mothim
mothim.entry_text: While it loves floral honey, it won’tgather any itself. Instead, itplots to steal some from Combee.  ~ Pokemon WHITE

combee.name: combee
combee.entry_text: It collects and delivers honey to its colony.At night, they cluster to form a beehive and sleep.  ~ Pokemon ALPHA-SAPPHIRE

vespiquen.name: vespiquen
vespiquen.entry_text: It skillfully commands its grubs in battles with itsenemies. The grubs are willing to risk their livesto defend Vespiquen.  ~ Pokemon SWORD

pachirisu.name: pachirisu
pachirisu.entry_text: A pair may be seen rubbing theircheek pouches together in aneffort to share stored electricity.  ~ Pokemon BLACK-2

buizel.name: buizel
buizel.entry_text: It inflates the flotation sac around its neck andpokes its head out of the water to see what isgoing on.  ~ Pokemon Y

floatzel.name: floatzel
floatzel.entry_text: It floats using its well-developed flotation sac.It assists in the rescues of drowning people.  ~ Pokemon OMEGA-RUBY

cherubi.name: cherubi
cherubi.entry_text: It evolves by sucking the energyout of the small ball where it hadbeen storing nutrients.  ~ Pokemon HEARTGOLD

cherrim.name: cherrim
cherrim.entry_text: If it senses strong sunlight, itopens its folded petals to absorbthe sun’s rays with its whole body.  ~ Pokemon BLACK-2

shellos.name: shellos
shellos.entry_text: When it senses danger, a purple liquid oozes outof it. The liquid is thought to be something likegreasy sweat.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-MOON

gastrodon.name: gastrodon
gastrodon.entry_text: Long ago, its entire back wasshielded with a sturdy shell. Thereare traces of it left in its cells.  ~ Pokemon WHITE-2

ambipom.name: ambipom
ambipom.entry_text: Split into two, the tails are soadept at handling and doing things,Ambipom rarely uses its hands.  ~ Pokemon BLACK-2

drifloon.name: drifloon
drifloon.entry_text: It is whispered that any child whomistakes DRIFLOON for a balloon andholds on to it could wind up missing.  ~ Pokemon SOULSILVER

drifblim.name: drifblim
drifblim.entry_text: There was once an incident in which a mantook a trip riding a Drifblim, only to go missing.  ~ Pokemon SUN

buneary.name: buneary
buneary.entry_text: If both of Buneary’s ears are rolled up, somethingis wrong with its body or mind. It’s a sure sign thePokémon is in need of care.  ~ Pokemon SWORD

lopunny.name: lopunny
lopunny.entry_text: Lopunny regrows its coat twice a year. Mufflersand hats made from its fur are really warm.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-SUN

mismagius.name: mismagius
mismagius.entry_text: Its cry sounds like an incantation.It is said the cry may rarely beimbued with happiness-giving power.  ~ Pokemon WHITE

honchkrow.name: honchkrow
honchkrow.entry_text: Becoming active at night, it isknown to swarm with numerousMURKROW in tow.  ~ Pokemon DIAMOND

glameow.name: glameow
glameow.entry_text: When it’s happy, GLAMEOWdemonstrates beautiful movementsof its tail, like a dancing ribbon.  ~ Pokemon HEARTGOLD

purugly.name: purugly
purugly.entry_text: It would claim another Pokémon’snest as its own if it finds a nestsufficiently comfortable.  ~ Pokemon SOULSILVER

chingling.name: chingling
chingling.entry_text: There is an orb inside its mouth.When it hops, the orb bounces allover and makes a ringing sound.  ~ Pokemon WHITE-2

stunky.name: stunky
stunky.entry_text: It sprays a foul fluid from itsrear. Its stench spreads over amile radius, driving Pokémon away.  ~ Pokemon WHITE

skuntank.name: skuntank
skuntank.entry_text: It sprays a vile-smelling fluidfrom the tip of its tail to attack.Its range is over 160 feet.  ~ Pokemon DIAMOND

bronzor.name: bronzor
bronzor.entry_text: Ancient people believed that thepattern on BRONZOR’s backcontained a mysterious power.  ~ Pokemon SOULSILVER

bronzong.name: bronzong
bronzong.entry_text: One caused a news sensation whenit was dug up at a constructionsite after a 2,000-year sleep.  ~ Pokemon DIAMOND

bonsly.name: bonsly
bonsly.entry_text: It prefers an arid atmosphere. Itleaks water that looks like tearswhen adjusting its moisture level.  ~ Pokemon BLACK-2

mime-jr.name: mime-jr
mime-jr.entry_text: It mimics the expressions andmotions of those it sees tounderstand the feelings of others.  ~ Pokemon WHITE

happiny.name: happiny
happiny.entry_text: It likes to carry around a smallrock. It may wander around others’feet and cause them to stumble.  ~ Pokemon BLACK-2

chatot.name: chatot
chatot.entry_text: It can learn and speak human words. If they gather,they all learn the same saying.  ~ Pokemon Y

spiritomb.name: spiritomb
spiritomb.entry_text: It was bound to a fissure in an odd keystone aspunishment for misdeeds 500 years ago.  ~ Pokemon Y

gible.name: gible
gible.entry_text: It nests in horizontal holes warmed by geothermalheat. Foes who get too close can expect to bepounced on and bitten.  ~ Pokemon X

gabite.name: gabite
gabite.entry_text: It habitually digs up and hoardsgems in its nest. Its loot isconstantly targeted by thieves.  ~ Pokemon PEARL

garchomp.name: garchomp
garchomp.entry_text: It is said that when one runs athigh speed, its wings create bladesof wind that can fell nearby trees.  ~ Pokemon BLACK

munchlax.name: munchlax
munchlax.entry_text: Anything that looks edible, Munchlax will go onand swallow whole. Its stomach is tough enoughto handle it even if the food has gone rotten.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-MOON

riolu.name: riolu
riolu.entry_text: It has the peculiar power of beingable to see emotions such as joyand rage in the form of waves.  ~ Pokemon WHITE

lucario.name: lucario
lucario.entry_text: By reading the auras of all things,it can tell how others are feelingfrom over half a mile away.  ~ Pokemon BLACK-2

hippopotas.name: hippopotas
hippopotas.entry_text: It lives in arid places. Insteadof perspiration, it expels grainysand from its body.  ~ Pokemon DIAMOND

hippowdon.name: hippowdon
hippowdon.entry_text: It blasts internally stored sand from ports on itsbody to create a towering twister for attack.  ~ Pokemon ALPHA-SAPPHIRE

skorupi.name: skorupi
skorupi.entry_text: It burrows under the sand to lie in wait for prey.Its tail claws can inject its prey with asavage poison.  ~ Pokemon Y

drapion.name: drapion
drapion.entry_text: It takes pride in its strength. Even though it cantear foes apart, it finishes them off withpowerful poison.  ~ Pokemon OMEGA-RUBY

croagunk.name: croagunk
croagunk.entry_text: Inflating its poison sacs, itmakes an eerie blubbering soundfor intimidation.  ~ Pokemon PEARL

toxicroak.name: toxicroak
toxicroak.entry_text: The toxin made in its poison sacsis pumped to the knuckle clawsthrough tubes down its arms.  ~ Pokemon PEARL

carnivine.name: carnivine
carnivine.entry_text: It binds itself to trees in marshes.It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling drool and gulps them down.  ~ Pokemon BLACK

finneon.name: finneon
finneon.entry_text: After long exposure to sunlight, the patterns on itstail fins shine vividly when darkness arrives.  ~ Pokemon Y

lumineon.name: lumineon
lumineon.entry_text: It crawls along the seafloor usingits long front fins like legs. Itcompetes for food with Lanturn.  ~ Pokemon BLACK

mantyke.name: mantyke
mantyke.entry_text: Mantyke living in Galar seem to be somewhatsluggish. The colder waters of the seas in thisregion may be the cause.  ~ Pokemon SWORD

snover.name: snover
snover.entry_text: It lives on snowy mountains. It sinks its legs intothe snow to absorb water and keep its owntemperature down.  ~ Pokemon SWORD

abomasnow.name: abomasnow
