stunfisk.name: stunfisk
stunfisk.entry_text: Its skin is very hard, so it is unhurt even if steppedon by sumo wrestlers. It smiles whentransmitting electricity.  ~ Pokemon OMEGA-RUBY

mienfoo.name: mienfoo
mienfoo.entry_text: They can often be seen in packs in the morning,slowly moving their bodies through a seriesof poses.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-SUN

mienshao.name: mienshao
mienshao.entry_text: It wields the fur on its arms like a whip.Its arm attacks come with such rapiditythat they cannot even be seen.  ~ Pokemon BLACK

druddigon.name: druddigon
druddigon.entry_text: Druddigon are vicious and cunning. They take upresidence in nests dug out by other Pokémon,treating the stolen nests as their own lairs.  ~ Pokemon SHIELD

golett.name: golett
golett.entry_text: The energy that burns inside it enables it to move,but no one has yet been able to identifythis energy.  ~ Pokemon X

golurk.name: golurk
golurk.entry_text: When the seal on its chest is removed, it ragesindiscriminately, turning the whole town aroundit into a mountain of rubble.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-MOON

pawniard.name: pawniard
pawniard.entry_text: Ignoring their injuries, groups attackby sinking the blades that cover theirbodies into their prey.  ~ Pokemon WHITE-2

bisharp.name: bisharp
bisharp.entry_text: This pitiless Pokémon commands a group ofPawniard to hound prey into immobility. It thenmoves in to finish the prey off.  ~ Pokemon X

bouffalant.name: bouffalant
bouffalant.entry_text: They are known to charge so wildlythat if a train were to enter theirterritory, they would send it flying.  ~ Pokemon WHITE-2

rufflet.name: rufflet
rufflet.entry_text: It stands up to massive opponents, notout of courage, but out of recklessness.But that is how it gets stronger.  ~ Pokemon BLACK-2

braviary.name: braviary
braviary.entry_text: For the sake of its friends, this brave warrior of thesky will not stop battling, even if injured.  ~ Pokemon X

vullaby.name: vullaby
vullaby.entry_text: Its wings are too tiny to allow it to fly. As the timeapproaches for it to evolve, it discards the bonesit was wearing.  ~ Pokemon X

mandibuzz.name: mandibuzz
mandibuzz.entry_text: Watching from the sky, they swoop to strikeweakened Pokémon on the ground. They decoratethemselves with bones.  ~ Pokemon Y

heatmor.name: heatmor
heatmor.entry_text: It draws in air through its tail, transforms it into fire,and uses it like a tongue. It melts Durant andeats them.  ~ Pokemon ALPHA-SAPPHIRE

durant.name: durant
durant.entry_text: They attack in groups, coveringthemselves in steel armor toprotect themselves from Heatmor.  ~ Pokemon BLACK

deino.name: deino
deino.entry_text: Lacking sight, it’s unaware of itssurroundings, so it bumps into thingsand eats anything that moves.  ~ Pokemon WHITE-2

zweilous.name: zweilous
zweilous.entry_text: Since their two heads do not get alongand compete with each other for food,they always eat too much.  ~ Pokemon WHITE

hydreigon.name: hydreigon
hydreigon.entry_text: The heads on their arms do not havebrains. They use all three heads toconsume and destroy everything.  ~ Pokemon WHITE

larvesta.name: larvesta
larvesta.entry_text: It protects itself with flame. Long years ago,people believed Larvesta had a nest on the sun.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-MOON

volcarona.name: volcarona
volcarona.entry_text: When volcanic ash darkened theatmosphere, it is said that Volcarona’sfire provided a replacement for the sun.  ~ Pokemon BLACK

cobalion.name: cobalion
cobalion.entry_text: It has a body and heart of steel.Its glare is sufficient to make evenan unruly Pokémon obey it.  ~ Pokemon WHITE

terrakion.name: terrakion
terrakion.entry_text: Spoken of in legend, this Pokémon used itsphenomenal power to destroy a castle in its effortto protect Pokémon.  ~ Pokemon Y

virizion.name: virizion
virizion.entry_text: Legends say this Pokémon confounded opponentswith its swift movements.  ~ Pokemon ALPHA-SAPPHIRE

tornadus.name: tornadus
tornadus.entry_text: The lower half of its body is wrapped ina cloud of energy. It zooms throughthe sky at 200 mph.  ~ Pokemon BLACK

thundurus.name: thundurus
thundurus.entry_text: As it flies around, it shoots lightning allover the place and causes forest fires.It is therefore disliked.  ~ Pokemon BLACK-2

reshiram.name: reshiram
reshiram.entry_text: According to myth, if people ignore truth andlet themselves become consumed by greed,Reshiram will arrive to burn their kingdoms down.  ~ Pokemon SHIELD

zekrom.name: zekrom
zekrom.entry_text: This legendary Pokémon can scorchthe world with lightning. It assiststhose who want to build an ideal world.  ~ Pokemon BLACK-2

landorus.name: landorus
landorus.entry_text: Lands visited by Landorus grant suchbountiful crops that it has been hailedas “The Guardian of the Fields.”  ~ Pokemon BLACK

kyurem.name: kyurem
kyurem.entry_text: It generates a powerful, freezing energy insideitself, but its body became frozen when the energyleaked out.  ~ Pokemon Y

keldeo.name: keldeo
keldeo.entry_text: When it is resolute, its body fills with power and itbecomes swifter. Its jumps are then too fastto follow.  ~ Pokemon ALPHA-SAPPHIRE

meloetta.name: meloetta
meloetta.entry_text: Its melodies are sung with a special vocalizationmethod that can control the feelings of those whohear it.  ~ Pokemon ALPHA-SAPPHIRE

genesect.name: genesect
genesect.entry_text: This Pokémon existed 300 million yearsago. Team Plasma altered it andattached a cannon to its back.  ~ Pokemon WHITE-2

chespin.name: chespin
chespin.entry_text: Such a thick shell of wood covers its head and backthat even a direct hit from a truck wouldn’t faze it.  ~ Pokemon ALPHA-SAPPHIRE

quilladin.name: quilladin
quilladin.entry_text: They strengthen their lower bodies byrunning into one another. They are verykind and won’t start fights.  ~ Pokemon ALPHA-SAPPHIRE

chesnaught.name: chesnaught
chesnaught.entry_text: Its Tackle is forceful enough to flip a 50-ton tank.It shields its allies from danger with its own body.  ~ Pokemon OMEGA-RUBY

fennekin.name: fennekin
fennekin.entry_text: Eating a twig fills it with energy,and its roomy ears give vent to airhotter than 390 degrees Fahrenheit.  ~ Pokemon OMEGA-RUBY

braixen.name: braixen
braixen.entry_text: When the twig is plucked from its tail,friction sets the twig alight. The flameis used to send signals to its allies.  ~ Pokemon ALPHA-SAPPHIRE

delphox.name: delphox
delphox.entry_text: Using psychic power, it generates afiery vortex of 5,400 degrees Fahrenheit,incinerating foes swept into this whirl of flame.  ~ Pokemon ALPHA-SAPPHIRE

froakie.name: froakie
froakie.entry_text: It protects its skin by covering its body indelicate bubbles. Beneath its happy-go-lucky air,it keeps a watchful eye on its surroundings.  ~ Pokemon ALPHA-SAPPHIRE

frogadier.name: frogadier
frogadier.entry_text: Its swiftness is unparalleled.It can scale a tower of morethan 2,000 feet in a minute’s time.  ~ Pokemon ALPHA-SAPPHIRE

greninja.name: greninja
greninja.entry_text: It appears and vanishes with a ninja’s grace.It toys with its enemies using swift movements, whileslicing them with throwing stars of sharpest water.  ~ Pokemon Y

bunnelby.name: bunnelby
bunnelby.entry_text: It has ears like shovels. Digging holesstrengthens its ears so much that theycan sever thick roots effortlessly.  ~ Pokemon Y

diggersby.name: diggersby
diggersby.entry_text: The fur on its belly retains heat exceptionallywell. People used to make heavy winter clothingfrom fur shed by this Pokémon.  ~ Pokemon SHIELD

fletchling.name: fletchling
fletchling.entry_text: These friendly Pokémon send signalsto one another with beautiful chirpsand tail-feather movements.  ~ Pokemon X

fletchinder.name: fletchinder
fletchinder.entry_text: Fletchinder are exceedingly territorial andaggressive. These Pokémon fight amongthemselves over feeding grounds.  ~ Pokemon SHIELD

talonflame.name: talonflame
talonflame.entry_text: In the fever of an exciting battle, itshowers embers from the gaps betweenits feathers and takes to the air.  ~ Pokemon X

scatterbug.name: scatterbug
scatterbug.entry_text: The powder that covers its bodyregulates its temperature, so itcan live in any region or climate.  ~ Pokemon Y

spewpa.name: spewpa
spewpa.entry_text: It lives hidden within thicket shadows.When predators attack, it quickly bristles the furcovering its body in an effort to threaten them.  ~ Pokemon X

vivillon.name: vivillon
vivillon.entry_text: The patterns on this Pokémon’s wingsdepend on the climate and topographyof its habitat. It scatters colorful scales.  ~ Pokemon Y

litleo.name: litleo
litleo.entry_text: The stronger the opponent it faces,the more heat surges from its maneand the more power flows through its body.  ~ Pokemon OMEGA-RUBY

pyroar.name: pyroar
pyroar.entry_text: The male with the largest mane of fireis the leader of the pride.  ~ Pokemon OMEGA-RUBY

flabebe.name: flabebe
flabebe.entry_text: Flabébé wears a crown made from pollen it’scollected from its flower. The crown has hiddenhealing properties.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-MOON

floette.name: floette
floette.entry_text: When the flowers of a well-tended flower bed bloom,it appears and celebrates with an elegant dance.  ~ Pokemon Y

florges.name: florges
florges.entry_text: In times long past, governors of castleswould invite Florges to create flower gardensto embellish the castle domains.  ~ Pokemon Y

skiddo.name: skiddo
skiddo.entry_text: Thought to be one of the first Pokémon to live inharmony with humans, it has a placid disposition.  ~ Pokemon OMEGA-RUBY

gogoat.name: gogoat
gogoat.entry_text: It can tell how its Trainer is feeling bysubtle shifts in the grip on its horns.This empathic sense lets them run as if one being.  ~ Pokemon OMEGA-RUBY

pancham.name: pancham
pancham.entry_text: It does its level best to glare and pull a scary face,but it can’t help grinning if anyone pats its head.  ~ Pokemon ALPHA-SAPPHIRE

pangoro.name: pangoro
pangoro.entry_text: Using its leaf, Pangoro can predict the moves ofits opponents. It strikes with punches that canturn a dump truck into scrap with just one hit.  ~ Pokemon SHIELD

furfrou.name: furfrou
furfrou.entry_text: Left alone, its fur will grow longer and longer,but it will only allow someone it trusts to cut it.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-MOON

espurr.name: espurr
espurr.entry_text: The organ that emits its intense psychic power issheltered by its ears to keep power from leaking out.  ~ Pokemon OMEGA-RUBY

meowstic.name: meowstic
meowstic.entry_text: If it doesn’t hold back when it unleashes itspsychic power, it can tear apart a tanker.Its unfriendliness is part of its charm.  ~ Pokemon SHIELD

honedge.name: honedge
honedge.entry_text: Apparently this Pokémon is born when adeparted spirit inhabits a sword. It attaches itselfto people and drinks their life force.  ~ Pokemon OMEGA-RUBY

doublade.name: doublade
doublade.entry_text: When Honedge evolves, it divides into two swords,which cooperate via telepathy to coordinate attacksand slash their enemies to ribbons.  ~ Pokemon OMEGA-RUBY

aegislash.name: aegislash
aegislash.entry_text: Once upon a time, a king with an Aegislashreigned over the land. His Pokémon eventuallydrained him of life, and his kingdom fell with him.  ~ Pokemon SHIELD

spritzee.name: spritzee
spritzee.entry_text: In the past, rather than using perfume,royal ladies carried a Spritzeethat would waft a fragrance they liked.  ~ Pokemon Y

aromatisse.name: aromatisse
aromatisse.entry_text: Its scent is so overpowering that, unless a Trainerhappens to really enjoy the smell, he or she willhave a hard time walking alongside it.  ~ Pokemon Y

swirlix.name: swirlix
swirlix.entry_text: To entangle its opponents in battle, it extrudeswhite threads as sweet and sticky as cotton candy.  ~ Pokemon OMEGA-RUBY

slurpuff.name: slurpuff
slurpuff.entry_text: By taking in a person’s scent, it can sniff out theirmental and physical condition. It’s hoped thatthis skill will have many medical applications.  ~ Pokemon SWORD

inkay.name: inkay
inkay.entry_text: It flashes the light-emitting spots on its body,which drains its opponent’s will to fight.It takes the opportunity to scuttle away and hide.  ~ Pokemon ALPHA-SAPPHIRE

malamar.name: malamar
malamar.entry_text: When it comes to strong hypnosis, there’s anendless number of people who utilize Malamarfor their nefarious deeds.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-SUN

binacle.name: binacle
binacle.entry_text: They stretch and then contract, yanking theirrocks along with them in bold hops. They eatseaweed that washes up on the shoreline.  ~ Pokemon Y

barbaracle.name: barbaracle
barbaracle.entry_text: When they evolve, two Binacle multiply into seven.They fight with the power of seven Binacle.  ~ Pokemon X

skrelp.name: skrelp
skrelp.entry_text: Camouflaged as rotten kelp, they sprayliquid poison on prey that approachesunawares and then finish it off.  ~ Pokemon X

dragalge.name: dragalge
dragalge.entry_text: This vicious Pokémon sprays a poisonous liquidon opponents that come near. For whateverreason, it gets along really well with Dhelmise.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-SUN

clauncher.name: clauncher
clauncher.entry_text: By detonating gas that accumulates in its rightclaw, this Pokémon launches water like a bullet.This is how Clauncher defeats its enemies.  ~ Pokemon SHIELD

clawitzer.name: clawitzer
clawitzer.entry_text: After using the feelers on its oversized claw todetect the location of prey, Clawitzer launchesa cannonball of water at its target.  ~ Pokemon SWORD

helioptile.name: helioptile
helioptile.entry_text: The frills on either side of its head have cellsthat generate electricity when exposed to sunlight.  ~ Pokemon ALPHA-SAPPHIRE

heliolisk.name: heliolisk
heliolisk.entry_text: One Heliolisk basking in the sun with its frilloutspread is all it would take to produce enoughelectricity to power a city.  ~ Pokemon SHIELD

tyrunt.name: tyrunt
tyrunt.entry_text: Tyrunt is spoiled and selfish. It may just betrying to frolic, but sometimes the ones it’strying to frolic with are gravely injured.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-MOON

tyrantrum.name: tyrantrum
tyrantrum.entry_text: Complete restoration is impossible, allowingroom for theories that its entire body wasonce covered in a feather-like coat.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-SUN

amaura.name: amaura
amaura.entry_text: Amaura was restored successfully, but it’s notexpected to live long because of the heat of thecurrent environment.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-MOON

aurorus.name: aurorus
aurorus.entry_text: Using its diamond-shaped crystals,it can instantly create a wall ofice to block an opponent’s attack.  ~ Pokemon ALPHA-SAPPHIRE

sylveon.name: sylveon
sylveon.entry_text: It sends a soothing aura from itsribbonlike feelers to calm fights.  ~ Pokemon OMEGA-RUBY

hawlucha.name: hawlucha
hawlucha.entry_text: It drives its opponents to exhaustion with its agilemaneuvers, then ends the fight with a flashyfinishing move.  ~ Pokemon SWORD

dedenne.name: dedenne
dedenne.entry_text: Its upper whiskers are sensors that survey itssurroundings. Its lower whiskers are organsthat shoot electricity.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-MOON

carbink.name: carbink
carbink.entry_text: Born from the high temperatures and pressuresdeep underground, it defends itself by firingbeams from the jewel part of its body.  ~ Pokemon SUN

goomy.name: goomy
goomy.entry_text: It’s covered in a slimy membrane that makesany punches or kicks slide off it harmlessly.  ~ Pokemon ALPHA-SAPPHIRE

sliggoo.name: sliggoo
sliggoo.entry_text: The lump on its back contains its tiny brain.It thinks only of food and escaping its enemies.  ~ Pokemon SHIELD

goodra.name: goodra
goodra.entry_text: It attacks with retractable horns.It throws a punch that’s the equivalentof the force of a hundred pro boxers.  ~ Pokemon ALPHA-SAPPHIRE

klefki.name: klefki
klefki.entry_text: It never lets go of a key that it likes,so people give it the keys to vaults andsafes as a way to prevent crime.  ~ Pokemon ALPHA-SAPPHIRE

phantump.name: phantump
phantump.entry_text: According to old tales, these Pokémon arestumps possessed by the spirits ofchildren who died while lost in the forest.  ~ Pokemon ALPHA-SAPPHIRE

trevenant.name: trevenant
trevenant.entry_text: Small roots that extend from the tips of thisPokémon’s feet can tie into the trees of theforest and give Trevenant control over them.  ~ Pokemon SHIELD

pumpkaboo.name: pumpkaboo
pumpkaboo.entry_text: When taking spirits to the afterlife, largePumpkaboo prefer the spirits of adults tothose of children.  ~ Pokemon SWORD

gourgeist.name: gourgeist
gourgeist.entry_text: Large Gourgeist put on the guise of adults,taking the hands of children to lead them tothe afterlife.  ~ Pokemon SWORD

bergmite.name: bergmite
bergmite.entry_text: Using air of -150 degrees Fahrenheit, theyfreeze opponents solid. They live in herdsabove the snow line on mountains.  ~ Pokemon ALPHA-SAPPHIRE

avalugg.name: avalugg
avalugg.entry_text: At high latitudes, this Pokémon can be foundwith clusters of Bergmite on its back as it swimsamong the icebergs.  ~ Pokemon SWORD

noibat.name: noibat
noibat.entry_text: No wavelength of sound is beyond Noibat’sability to produce. The ultrasonic waves itgenerates can overcome much larger Pokémon.  ~ Pokemon SHIELD

noivern.name: noivern
noivern.entry_text: They fly around on moonless nightsand attack careless prey. Nothing canbeat them in a battle in the dark.  ~ Pokemon OMEGA-RUBY

xerneas.name: xerneas
xerneas.entry_text: When the horns on its head shinein seven colors, it is said to besharing everlasting life.  ~ Pokemon ALPHA-SAPPHIRE

yveltal.name: yveltal
yveltal.entry_text: When this legendary Pokémon’s wings andtail feathers spread wide and glow red,it absorbs the life force of living creatures.  ~ Pokemon OMEGA-RUBY

zygarde.name: zygarde
zygarde.entry_text: This is Zygarde’s form when about half of itspieces have been assembled. It plays the role ofmonitoring the ecosystem.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-SUN

diancie.name: diancie
diancie.entry_text: It can instantly create many diamondsby compressing the carbon in the airbetween its hands.  ~ Pokemon Y

hoopa.name: hoopa
hoopa.entry_text: This troublemaker sends anythingand everything to faraway placesusing its loop, which can warp space.  ~ Pokemon X

volcanion.name: volcanion
volcanion.entry_text: It lets out billows of steam and disappears intothe dense fog. It’s said to live in mountainswhere humans do not tread.  ~ Pokemon X

rowlet.name: rowlet
rowlet.entry_text: It feels relaxed in tight, dark places and hasbeen known to use its Trainer’s pocket or bagas a nest.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-MOON

dartrix.name: dartrix
dartrix.entry_text: A bit of a dandy, it spends its free timepreening its wings. Its preoccupation with anydirt on its plumage can leave it unable to battle.  ~ Pokemon SUN

decidueye.name: decidueye
decidueye.entry_text: As if wielding a bow, it launches the arrow quillshidden among the feathers of its wings.Decidueye’s shots never miss.  ~ Pokemon SWORD

litten.name: litten
litten.entry_text: Its coat regrows twice a year. When the timecomes, Litten sets its own body on fire andburns away the old fur.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-MOON

torracat.name: torracat
torracat.entry_text: It can act spoiled if it grows close to its Trainer.A powerful Pokémon, its sharp claws can leaveits Trainer’s whole body covered in scratches.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-SUN

incineroar.name: incineroar
incineroar.entry_text: When its fighting spirit is set alight, the flamesaround its waist become especially intense.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-MOON

popplio.name: popplio
popplio.entry_text: It creates special bouncy balloons to send at itsopponents. When the balloons pop, the sheerforce of their bursting is what deals damage.  ~ Pokemon SWORD

brionne.name: brionne
brionne.entry_text: As if dancing, it artfully dodges the attacks of itsenemies. All the while, it’s busy forming a bunchof balloons to overwhelm its foes.  ~ Pokemon SWORD

primarina.name: primarina
primarina.entry_text: To Primarina, every battle is a stage. It takesdown its prey with beautiful singingand dancing.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-SUN

pikipek.name: pikipek
pikipek.entry_text: This Pokémon feeds on berries, whose leftoverseeds become the ammunition for the attacks itfires off from its mouth.  ~ Pokemon MOON

trumbeak.name: trumbeak
trumbeak.entry_text: By bending its beak, it can produce a variety ofcalls and brand itself a noisy nuisance forits neighbors.  ~ Pokemon MOON

toucannon.name: toucannon
toucannon.entry_text: Known for forming harmonious couples, thisPokémon is brought to wedding ceremonies as agood luck charm.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-MOON

yungoos.name: yungoos
yungoos.entry_text: Its stomach takes up most of its long torso.It’s a big eater, so the amount Trainers have tospend on its food is no laughing matter.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-SUN

gumshoos.name: gumshoos
gumshoos.entry_text: It adores having Rattata and Raticate for dinner,but as it’s diurnal, it never encounters them.This Pokémon boasts incredible patience.  ~ Pokemon MOON

grubbin.name: grubbin
grubbin.entry_text: Its strong jaw enables it to scrape trees andslurp out the sap. It normally lives underground.  ~ Pokemon SUN

charjabug.name: charjabug
charjabug.entry_text: Its digestive processes convert the leaves it eatsinto electricity. An electric sac in its belly storesthe electricity for later use.  ~ Pokemon SHIELD

vikavolt.name: vikavolt
vikavolt.entry_text: If it carries a Charjabug to use as a spare battery,a flying Vikavolt can rapidly fire high-poweredbeams of electricity.  ~ Pokemon SHIELD

crabrawler.name: crabrawler
crabrawler.entry_text: Its hard pincers are well suited to both offenseand defense. Fights between two Crabrawlerare like boxing matches.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-SUN

crabominable.name: crabominable
crabominable.entry_text: Before it stops to think, it just starts pummeling.There are records of its turning backavalanches with a flurry of punches.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-MOON

oricorio.name: oricorio
oricorio.entry_text: This Oricorio has drunk red nectar. If its Trainergives the wrong order, this passionate Pokémonbecomes fiercely angry.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-MOON

cutiefly.name: cutiefly
cutiefly.entry_text: Myriads of Cutiefly flutter above the heads ofpeople who have auras resembling thoseof flowers.  ~ Pokemon MOON

ribombee.name: ribombee
ribombee.entry_text: It rolls up pollen into puffs. It makes manydifferent varieties, some used as food andothers used in battle.  ~ Pokemon SUN

rockruff.name: rockruff
rockruff.entry_text: When it rubs the rocks on its neck against you,that’s proof of its love for you. However, therocks are sharp, so the gesture is quite painful!  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-MOON

lycanroc.name: lycanroc
lycanroc.entry_text: This form of Lycanroc is normally calm and quiet.Once a battle begins, however, this Pokémondisplays a ferocious fighting spirit.  ~ Pokemon SWORD

wishiwashi.name: wishiwashi
wishiwashi.entry_text: On their own, they’re very weak. But whenWishiwashi pool their power together in aschool, they become a demon of the sea.  ~ Pokemon SWORD

mareanie.name: mareanie
mareanie.entry_text: Aside from its head, its body partsregenerate quickly if they’re cut off. After agood night’s sleep, Mareanie is back to normal.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-MOON

toxapex.name: toxapex
toxapex.entry_text: Those attacked by Toxapex’s poison will sufferintense pain for three days and three nights.Post-recovery, there will be some aftereffects.  ~ Pokemon MOON

mudbray.name: mudbray
mudbray.entry_text: It has a stubborn, individualistic disposition.Eating dirt, making mud, and playing in the mireall form part of its daily routine.  ~ Pokemon MOON

mudsdale.name: mudsdale
mudsdale.entry_text: Mudsdale has so much stamina that it could carryover 10 tons across the Galar region without restor sleep.  ~ Pokemon SHIELD

dewpider.name: dewpider
dewpider.entry_text: It crawls onto the land in search of food.Its water bubble allows it to breathe andprotects its soft head.  ~ Pokemon SUN

araquanid.name: araquanid
araquanid.entry_text: It launches water bubbles with its legs, drowningprey within the bubbles. This Pokémon can thentake its time to savor its meal.  ~ Pokemon SWORD

fomantis.name: fomantis
fomantis.entry_text: During the day, it sleeps and soaks up light.When night falls, it walks around lookingfor a safer place to sleep.  ~ Pokemon SUN

lurantis.name: lurantis
lurantis.entry_text: It requires a lot of effort to maintain Lurantis’svivid coloring, but some collectors enjoy thiswork and treat it as their hobby.  ~ Pokemon SUN

morelull.name: morelull
morelull.entry_text: Pokémon living in the forest eat thedelicious caps on Morelull’s head.The caps regrow overnight.  ~ Pokemon SWORD

shiinotic.name: shiinotic
shiinotic.entry_text: Its flickering spores lure in prey and put them tosleep. Once this Pokémon has its prey snoozing,it drains their vitality with its fingertips.  ~ Pokemon SWORD

salandit.name: salandit
salandit.entry_text: This sneaky Pokémon will slink behind its preyand immobilize it with poisonous gas before theprey even realizes Salandit is there.  ~ Pokemon SHIELD

salazzle.name: salazzle
salazzle.entry_text: Only female Salazzle exist. They emit a gas ladenwith pheromones to captivate male Salandit.  ~ Pokemon SWORD

stufful.name: stufful
stufful.entry_text: Its fluffy fur is a delight to pet, but carelesslyreaching out to touch this Pokémon could resultin painful retaliation.  ~ Pokemon SWORD

bewear.name: bewear
bewear.entry_text: This Pokémon has the habit of hugging itscompanions. Many Trainers have left this worldafter their spines were squashed by its hug.  ~ Pokemon MOON

bounsweet.name: bounsweet
bounsweet.entry_text: When under attack, it secretes a sweetand delicious sweat. The scent only callsmore enemies to it.  ~ Pokemon SHIELD

steenee.name: steenee
steenee.entry_text: The sepals on its head developed to protect itsbody. These are quite hard, so even if peckedby bird Pokémon, this Pokémon is totally fine.  ~ Pokemon SUN

tsareena.name: tsareena
tsareena.entry_text: A master of grand and beautiful kicks, it canknock out even kickboxing champions with asingle blow.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-SUN

comfey.name: comfey
comfey.entry_text: These Pokémon smell very nice. All Comfey weardifferent flowers, so each of these Pokémon hasits own individual scent.  ~ Pokemon SHIELD

oranguru.name: oranguru
oranguru.entry_text: It knows the forest inside and out. If it comesacross a wounded Pokémon, Oranguru willgather medicinal herbs to treat it.  ~ Pokemon SHIELD

passimian.name: passimian
passimian.entry_text: They form groups of roughly 20 individuals.Their mutual bond is remarkable—they will neverlet down a comrade.  ~ Pokemon SUN

wimpod.name: wimpod
wimpod.entry_text: Wimpod gather in swarms, constantly on thelookout for danger. They scatter the momentthey detect an enemy’s presence.  ~ Pokemon SHIELD

golisopod.name: golisopod
golisopod.entry_text: The shell covering its body is as hard asdiamond. This Pokémon will do anything ittakes to win.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-SUN

sandygast.name: sandygast
sandygast.entry_text: It likes the shovel on its head, so Sandygastwill get serious and fight any children who cometo take it back.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-SUN

palossand.name: palossand
palossand.entry_text: Palossand is known as the Beach Nightmare. Itpulls its prey down into the sand by controllingthe sand itself, and then it sucks out their souls.  ~ Pokemon SWORD

pyukumuku.name: pyukumuku
pyukumuku.entry_text: Its entire body is covered in its own slime. If youaccidentally step on one, you’ll slip, and it willget mad and smack you!  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-MOON

type-null.name: type-null
type-null.entry_text: A Pokémon weapon developed for a specificmission, it went berserk during an experiment,so it was cryogenically frozen.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-SUN

silvally.name: silvally
silvally.entry_text: Thanks to its awakened powers, it can change tothe Ice type to match the memory ithas equipped.  ~ Pokemon SWORD

minior.name: minior
minior.entry_text: Originally making its home in the ozone layer,it hurtles to the ground when the shell enclosingits body grows too heavy.  ~ Pokemon SUN

komala.name: komala
komala.entry_text: It remains asleep from birth to death as a resultof the sedative properties of the leaves thatform its diet.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-MOON

turtonator.name: turtonator
turtonator.entry_text: Explosive substances coat the shell on its back.Enemies that dare attack it will be blown awayby an immense detonation.  ~ Pokemon SWORD

togedemaru.name: togedemaru
togedemaru.entry_text: The long hairs on its back act as lightning rods.The bolts of lightning it attracts are stored asenergy in its electric sac.  ~ Pokemon MOON

mimikyu.name: mimikyu
mimikyu.entry_text: A gust of wind revealed what hides under thisPokémon’s rag to a passing Trainer, who wenthome and died painfully that very night.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-MOON

bruxish.name: bruxish
bruxish.entry_text: Its skin is thick enough to fend off Mareanie’sspikes. With its robust teeth, Bruxish crunchesup the spikes and eats them.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-MOON

drampa.name: drampa
drampa.entry_text: This Pokémon is friendly to people and loveschildren most of all. It comes from deep in themountains to play with children it likes in town.  ~ Pokemon MOON

dhelmise.name: dhelmise
dhelmise.entry_text: It wraps its prey in green seaweed and sucksaway their vitality. It only likes to go after bigprey like Wailord.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-SUN

jangmo-o.name: jangmo-o
jangmo-o.entry_text: It will never show an enemy its back in battle.Ancient warriors liked Jangmo-o for its valiantdisposition and made it one of their own.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-MOON

hakamo-o.name: hakamo-o
hakamo-o.entry_text: The scaleless, scarred parts of its body aresigns of its strength. It shows them off todefeated opponents.  ~ Pokemon SWORD

kommo-o.name: kommo-o
kommo-o.entry_text: When it howls after finishing off its prey, themetallic sounds of its celebrating comrades canbe heard from all around.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-SUN

tapu-koko.name: tapu-koko
tapu-koko.entry_text: It confuses its enemies by flying too quickly forthe eye to follow. It has a hair-trigger temperbut forgets what made it angry an instant later.  ~ Pokemon MOON

tapu-lele.name: tapu-lele
tapu-lele.entry_text: It heals the wounds of people and Pokémon bysprinkling them with its sparkling scales. Thisguardian deity is worshiped on Akala.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-SUN

tapu-bulu.name: tapu-bulu
tapu-bulu.entry_text: It makes ringing sounds with its tail to let othersknow where it is, avoiding unneeded conflicts.This guardian deity of Ula’ula controls plants.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-MOON

tapu-fini.name: tapu-fini
tapu-fini.entry_text: Although it’s called a guardian deity, terriblecalamities sometimes befall those whorecklessly approach Tapu Fini.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-MOON

cosmog.name: cosmog
cosmog.entry_text: Whether or not it’s a Pokémon from this worldis a mystery. When it’s in a jam, it warps awayto a safe place to hide.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-MOON

cosmoem.name: cosmoem
cosmoem.entry_text: The absorption of starlight fuels this Pokémon’sgrowth. The shell that encases it is harder thanany known material.  ~ Pokemon SWORD

solgaleo.name: solgaleo
solgaleo.entry_text: Sometimes the result of its opening an UltraWormhole is that energy and life-forms fromother worlds are called here to this world.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-SUN

lunala.name: lunala
lunala.entry_text: It sometimes summons unknown powers andlife-forms here to this world from holes thatlead to other worlds.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-MOON

nihilego.name: nihilego
nihilego.entry_text: A life-form from another world, it was dubbeda UB and is thought to produce astrong neurotoxin.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-SUN

buzzwole.name: buzzwole
buzzwole.entry_text: Although it’s alien to this world and a dangerhere, it’s apparently a common organism in theworld where it normally lives.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-SUN

pheromosa.name: pheromosa
pheromosa.entry_text: A life-form that lives in another world, its bodyis thin and supple, but it also possessesgreat power.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-SUN

xurkitree.name: xurkitree
xurkitree.entry_text: They’ve been dubbed Ultra Beasts. Some ofthem stand unmoving, like trees, with theirarms and legs stuck into the ground.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-MOON

celesteela.name: celesteela
celesteela.entry_text: It appeared from the Ultra Wormhole. Witnessesobserved it flying across the sky at high speed.  ~ Pokemon SUN

kartana.name: kartana
kartana.entry_text: This Ultra Beast’s body, which is as thin aspaper, is like a sharpened sword.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-SUN

guzzlord.name: guzzlord
guzzlord.entry_text: It has gobbled mountains and swallowed wholebuildings, according to reports. It’s one of theUltra Beasts.  ~ Pokemon SUN

magearna.name: magearna
magearna.entry_text: Built roughly 500 years ago by a scientist,the part called the Soul-Heart is theactual life-form.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-MOON

marshadow.name: marshadow
marshadow.entry_text: It slips into the shadows of others and mimicstheir powers and movements. As it improves, itbecomes stronger than those it’s imitating.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-SUN

poipole.name: poipole
poipole.entry_text: This Ultra Beast is well enough liked to bechosen as a first partner in its own world.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-SUN

naganadel.name: naganadel
naganadel.entry_text: One kind of Ultra Beast, it fires a glowing,venomous liquid from its needles. This liquidis also immensely adhesive.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-MOON

stakataka.name: stakataka
stakataka.entry_text: When stone walls started moving and attacking,the brute’s true identity was this mysteriouslife-form, which brings to mind an Ultra Beast.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-MOON

blacephalon.name: blacephalon
blacephalon.entry_text: It slithers toward people. Then, without warning,it triggers the explosion of its own head.It’s apparently one kind of Ultra Beast.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-SUN

zeraora.name: zeraora
zeraora.entry_text: It electrifies its claws and tears its opponentsapart with them. Even if they dodge its attack,they’ll be electrocuted by the flying sparks.  ~ Pokemon ULTRA-SUN
